Re: JSON-RPC password

Bitcointalk

2010-07-21 00:05:20 UTC - [11]Original Post

   Still need to know whatʼs the most typical settings file format on
   Linux.  Is there a standard file extension?  Iʼve never seen a settings
   file using JSON, and it doesnʼt look very human friendly with
   everything required to be in quotes.  I think what I usually see is
   like:
   # comment
   setting=value
   Is there a settings file thing in Boost?
   When youʼre using bitcoind to issue commands from the command line as a
   client, can we have it get the password from the settings file then
   too?
   Gavin pointed out I forgot to increment the column of numbers in
   CommandLineRPC, so the current -rpcpw= implementation doesnʼt work
   right from the command line with non-string parameters.  (JSON-RPC is
   fine)  Still under construction.
